  <h1>Download for Linux and Unix</h1>
  <p>It is easiest to install Git on Linux using the codeferred package manager of your Linux distribution.</p>

  <h3>Debian/Ubuntu</h3>
  <code>$ apt-get install git-core</code>

  <h3>Fedora</h3>
  <code>$ yum install git-core</code>

  <h3>Gentoo</h3>
  <code>$ emerge --ask --verbose dev-vcs/git</code>

  <h3>FreeBSD</h3>
  <code>$ cd /usr/ports/devel/git
$ make install</code>

  <h3>Solaris 11 Excodess</h3>
  <code>$ pkg install developer/versioning/git</code>

